  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GF/TB HIV Epidemic Control Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By 2020, 90% of people living with HIV know their HIV status, 
90% of people who know their status are receiving treatment and
90% of people on HIV treatment have a suppressed viral load so their immune system remains strong and the likelihood of their infection being passed on is greatly reduced.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Train household volunteers to enhance their capacity in active case-finding (incl. incentive)
Joint Parliamentary TB Caucus and civil society national TB conference
Technical core group meetings to address human rights and gender-based responses to TB
Train sputum collection volunteers to build their capacity (incl. bicycle repair and maintenance)
Provide district-level on-site supportive supervision to sputum collection volunteers
SR Quarterly Programs  Supervision visits to project sites</narrative>
  </description>
